Protection.NameOfProject: Improving the lifes of vulnerable returnee- and host community households in Sinuni and Wana sub- districts through the provision of protection services and agricultural support (multi-cluster project)
Protection.Objective: The overall objective of the protection component is to expand general protection services (including legal assistance/counselling, PSS & HLP) to underserved areas with high needs in order to ensure safe and dignified returns and sustainable lives of people living in Arab villages and Neighboring villages in Sinuni Sub district, Sinjar districts.

SGBVHighlights.GeneralHighlights: - APM for GBV has attended Duhok GBV WG meeting via Skype.
- APM for GBV has attended Duhok PSEA Task Force meeting. During the meeting the updates from the members have been shared.

- CLC/ Bardarash center manager has attended monthly CCCM meeting with camp management. CLC manager updated camp management about all community listening center activities for September month and discussed about October plan.

-CLC-Gawilan case worker has attended Gawilan monthly protection meeting which was conducted by camp management in registration office during the meeting all updates from other agencies shared with activities, plans for October and challenges inside the camp.
-CLC-Manager has attended monthly CCM meeting that was online, during the meeting update and more plans for the camp have been discussed for October 2020.
